Can anybody tell me were can I find a good school of IAIDO on the east
coast of the US. Thank you

Here is a link for a group that practices Muso Jikiden Eishin Ryu, all are
stand up guys.

_Jikishin-Kai: Traditional Japanese Martial Arts_
(http://www.jikishin-kai.com/)

Here is the link for the East Coast Representative

_Sakura Budokan- Traditional Martial Arts Instruction_
(http://www.sakurabudokan.com/)

Greg

messages.subject: Re: [samuraihistory] Iaido schools
messages.msgSnippet: The only person i could dierect you to is Master Wong Leung, but he travels up n down the east coast, last i checked, he was up in NY, but then again, the last
messages.messageBody:
The only person i could dierect you to is Master Wong Leung, but he travels up n down the east coast, last i checked, he was up in NY, but then again, the last time i checked was three years ago. His brother Sensei Koboushi Leung and him work in teaching MMA and WMA. I learned IAIDO, Kiserugama, and others from those two. But like i said last time i checked up on them was three years ago.
If you wish to check for them in NY, try the Bronx.



________________________________
